content=["<dl>",
"<dt><a href='#Section0'>Irritable bowel syndrome</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section0'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Often presents with intermittent and chronic history of diarrhoea.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Urinary 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid (5-HIAA) and chromogranin A will be normal.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section1'>Crohn's disease</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section1'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Right lower quadrant pain and peri-anal lesions. May also present with oral lesions.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Urinary 5-HIAA and chromogranin A will be normal.Inflammatory markers such as C-reactive protein may be elevated in Crohn's disease.Evidence of Crohn's disease on endoscopy.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section2'>Menopause</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section2'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> Amenorrhoea or irregular menstrual cycle; vaginal dryness, itching, and dyspareunia; pale, dry vaginal mucosa with decreased rugosity; mood changes.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Urinary 5-HIAA and chromogranin A will be normal. Gonadotropins (LH/FSH) will be elevated.</p>",
"</dd>",
"<dt><a href='#Section3'>Asthma</a></dt>",
"<dd id='Section3'>",
"<p><strong>Sign & Symptoms:</strong> If wheeze is the only symptom of myxoma carcinoid, then it may be mistaken for asthma. Absence of diarrhoea and abdominal pain.",
"<br><strong>Test:</strong> Urinary 5-HIAA and chromogranin A will be normal.</p>",
"</dd>",
"</dl>"].join("\n");